We're celebrating 5,000 stars on GitHub! Thank you to our wonderful community!

[Puck 0.16](https://github.com/measuredco/puck/releases) is a big release, introducing the headline permissions API and — you guessed it — quality of life improvements. This one took a while to put together, and we appreciate your patience and support.

- [**Permissions**](https://puckeditor.com/docs/integrating-puck/feature-toggling): Toggle Puck features like duplication, dragging, deletion through the new permissions and resolvePermissions APIs.
- [**Action bar override**](https://puckeditor.com/docs/api-reference/overrides/action-bar): Create custom action bars using the `actionBar` override, or extend the default one using the new [`<ActionBar>` component](https://puckeditor.com/docs/api-reference/components/action-bar).
- [**iframe style injection**](https://puckeditor.com/docs/api-reference/overrides/iframe): Access the iframe document to inject styles directly, or make other changes, via the new `iframe` override. We also introduced the [`emotion-cache` plugin](https://github.com/measuredco/puck/tree/main/packages/plugin-emotion-cache) for the common Emotion use-case.
- [**History injection**](https://puckeditor.com/docs/api-reference/components/puck#initialhistory): Inject the undo/redo history via the a series of new APIs
- [**React to actions**](https://puckeditor.com/docs/api-reference/components/puck#onactionaction-appstate-prevappstate): React to actions dispatched by Puck via the `onAction` callback.
- **Optional fields**: Optional props are no longer required to define in fields, since they may be defined dynamically.

Upgrade today or get started with:

```
npx create-puck-app@latest
```

## Permissions

[Permissions](https://puckeditor.com/docs/api-reference/permissions) enable you to [toggle core Puck functionality](https://puckeditor.com/docs/integrating-puck/feature-toggling) globally, on a per-component basis or dynamically.  Huge thanks to @xaviemirmon for his efforts on this.

```tsx
export function Editor() {
  return (
    <Puck
      permissions={{
        delete: false,
        duplicate: true
      }}
    />
  );
}
```
## Action bar override

The new [`actionBar` override](https://puckeditor.com/docs/api-reference/overrides/action-bar) enables you to create a custom action bar overlay, or extend the default one using the [`<ActionBar>` component](https://puckeditor.com/docs/api-reference/components/action-bar):

```tsx
const overrides = {
  actionBar: ({ children }) => (
    <ActionBar label="Actions">
      {/* Render default actions */}
      <ActionBar.Group>{children}</ActionBar.Group>

      {/* Render new actions */}
      <ActionBar.Group>
        <ActionBar.Action onClick={() => console.log("Clicked!")}>
          ★
        </ActionBar.Action>
      </ActionBar.Group>
    </ActionBar>
  ),
};
```
## iframe style injection

The [`iframe` override](https://puckeditor.com/docs/api-reference/overrides/iframe) enables you to access the iframe `document`, making it possible to inject styles into the head:

```tsx
const overrides = {
  iframe: ({ children, document }) => {
    useEffect(() => {
      if (document) {
        document.body.setAttribute("style", "background: hotpink;");
      }
    }, [document]);

    return <>{children}</>;
  },
};
```
The new [`emotion-cache` plugin](https://github.com/measuredco/puck/tree/main/packages/plugin-emotion-cache) uses this API to create an emotion cache inside the iframe, making Puck easy to use with any Emotion-based component library.

## History injection

Use the new history injection APIs to provide your own undo/redo history via the [`initialHistory` prop](https://puckeditor.com/docs/api-reference/components/puck#initialhistory), or dynamically via the [`setHistories` and `setHistoryIndex` functions](https://puckeditor.com/docs/api-reference/functions/use-puck#sethistories) from `usePuck().history`.

```tsx
const historyState = {
  data: {
    root: {
      props: { title: "My History" },
    },
  },
};

export function Editor() {
  return (
    <Puck
      initialHistory={{
        histories: [{ state: historyState }],
        index: 0,
      }}
      // ...
    />
  );
}
```
## React to actions

The [`onAction` API](https://puckeditor.com/docs/api-reference/components/puck#onactionaction-appstate-prevappstate) enables you to react to Puck’s internal actions as they’re dispatched:

```tsx
export function Editor() {
  return (
    <Puck
      onAction={(action, appState, prevAppState) => {
        if (action.type === "insert") {
          console.log("New component was inserted", appState);
        }
      }}
    />
  );
}
```
## Breaking changes

### `history.data` is now `history.state`

When using the usePuck `history` API, `data` is now renamed `state`.

### `history.id` is now optional (TypeScript)

When using the usePuck `history` API `id` is now optional. Puck will always generate an `id`, but TypeScript may complain.

### `lastData` is now returned as `null` instead of `{}` when empty in resolvers

When using the `lastData` option provided to `resolveData` or `resolveFields` functions, and there is no previous data, `lastData` will now be `null` instead of `{}`.

